<br>
She knew in the beginning that some amazons would be reluctant to accept Belle as their princess. Cora was Princess since Scynthia was brought back. Cora's place was not there though. . . Belle's was. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#993300>(5/13/01 8:53:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=AmazonWarMaskofDeath WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coronation of Princess Belle</span><hr size=1>  Dawn shook her head, but gave a smile. Dawn had her reasons for disliking the change more than ever. She had never met Cora, but Cora had been there,yes, from the start. Belle was just an intiate, half the Amazons didn't even know her! Why bring someone up into a princess position before you even know what she is like. You can hardly ever know when someone is going to be two faced. <p>Pyschotic injustice
